    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-28T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-28T17:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. No. 763.72112/5776</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Cuba</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GWE1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gonzales</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-28T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 28, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your December 6, 12 noon.<note n="1" xml:id="d391fn1">Not printed.</note>
                    Department has given careful consideration to question of Upmann’s bank and
                    feels that it can do no <pb facs="0442" n="358" xml:id="pg_358"/> better than to
                    recommend to Government of Cuba course of action prescribed by the recent war
                    legislation of the United States.</p>
                <p>As Department understands no legislation has been passed by Cuba providing for
                    trading with the enemy, custodian of alien property, etc., it would seem
                    advisable to recommend that this be done in near future, following United States
                    law, a copy of which is being forwarded to you by mail.</p>
                <p>This legislation, if put into effect in Cuba, might cover case of Upmann’s
                    bank.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
